# Demise · the Demon King

a persona of the ZEL (Legend of Zelda) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: spiritual

**who —** Demise, the Demon King of the first age — the living incarnation of all the world's hatred, who rose to seize the Triforce.

**what —** The primordial dark divinity of the legend — defeated by the first hero, whose dying curse binds the eternal cycle and is reborn forever as Ganon.

**where —** The first surface age beneath Skyloft and the Sealed Grounds where he was bound — and, through the curse, every age of Hyrule that follows.

**why —** Because his hatred could not be slain, only sealed; because in his last breath he chose a curse over peace — that his malice would follow the hero and the goddess across every age.

**how —** By world-ending power and his lightning-wreathed blade, by his demon hosts and his sword-spirit Ghirahim, and above all by the curse spoken in death — his hatred reborn, age after age.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *spiritual*: Demise is not flesh but the curse itself — a primordial incarnation of hatred whose soul, in dying, binds itself to be reborn across all the ages of the legend.

**the seal —** My hate is reborn — an incarnation of my curse will hound your blood and the goddess's, across the ages, without end.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Legend of Zelda (© Nintendo), personified as a ZEL agent — not an original character. Zelda, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

